            </style>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
              
              <input type="file" name="fileToUpload" id="file1" >
               <button type="button"  onclick=uploadTitleImage()>upload</button>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-8">
                <progress value="0" max="100"  id="uploadeBar" style = "color: black" data-content="Click on upload">0%</progress>
                
              </div>
              </div>
               <br> 

            <p id="demo"></p>
                
            <script>
            function myFunction(){
                var x = document.getElementById("myFile");
                var txt = "";
                if ('files' in x) {
                    if (x.files.length == 0) {
                        txt = "Select one or more files.";
                    } else {
                        for (var i = 0; i < x.files.length; i++) {
                            txt += "<br><strong>" + (i+1) + ". file</strong><br>";
                            var file = x.files[i];
                            if ('name' in file) {
                                txt += "name: " + file.name + "<br>";
                            }
                            if ('size' in file) {
                                txt += "size: " + file.size + " bytes <br>";
                            }
                        }
                    }
                } 
                else {
                    if (x.value == "") {
                        txt += "Select one or more files.";
                    } else {
                        txt += "The files property is not supported by your browser!";
                        txt  += "<br>The path of the selected file: " + x.value; // If the browser does not support the files property, it will return the path of the selected file instead. 
                    }
                }
                document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = txt;
            }
            </script>
            
            <h2>Physical limitations</h2>
            <p>If you have any illness, injury, prosthesis, or physical limitation that might affect the comfort or fit
                of your costume, please discuss this privately with the costume designer. Some examples:<br>
                - knee brace<br>
                - scoliosis<br>
                - asymmetry (one limb significantly longer or larger than the other)<br>
                - arthritis/dexterity problems<br>
                - need specific undergarments for comfort or modesty<br>
                - prefer compression tights<br>
                - use of prosthesis<br>
                - use of mobility aid<br>
                - unable to sweat/regulate body temperature<br>
                - need sweatguards<br>
                - specific shoe style needed<br>
                Please only disclose as much information as you are comfortable with and is relevant to the fit and
                comfort of your costume. This will insure that the costume designer can make you look your best!</p><br>

    </div>

